---

## ğŸš€ Getting Started

### 1. Clone or download
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/malware-scanner.git
cd malware-scanner
```

### 2. Create sample files
```powershell
# Benign file
'hello world' | Out-File -Encoding ascii .\samples\benign.txt

# Suspicious file
'User-Agent: EvilBot' | Out-File -Encoding ascii .\samples\suspicious.txt

# Fake EICAR file (safe substitute)
'FAKE-EICAR-STRING' | Out-File -Encoding ascii .\samples\fake_eicar.txt
```

### 3. Run the scanner
```bash
python scanner.py
```

---

## âœ… Example Output
```
[MATCH] samples\suspicious.txt -> ['SuspiciousAgent']
[MATCH] samples\fake_eicar.txt -> ['Fake_EICAR_Test']
```

---

## âš ï¸ Important Notes
- This project uses a **fake EICAR string** (`FAKE-EICAR-STRING`) to avoid antivirus interference.  
- Do **not** use real malware samples â€” this scanner is for **educational and demo purposes only**.  
- Extend it safely with regex, hex patterns, or entropy checks if you want more advanced detection.

